{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01DNTCrL3V8NqyGnVEH96H9n","type":"tool_result","content":"The file /Users/captain/code/github.com/polez/.ralph/fix_plan.md has been updated successfully."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"c9bd7957-c8f2-4e48-8fcc-7059d242854c","uuid":"b949ae87-dcf7-4950-923f-ef0b9c843482","tool_use_result":{"filePath":"/Users/captain/code/github.com/polez/.ralph/fix_plan.md","oldString":"- [ ] #4 - Replace `println!/eprintln!` with structured logging (tracing crate)\n  - At minimum: `src/gui/mod.rs` line 46 uses `println!`\n  - Scan entire codebase for println/eprintln and replace with `tracing::info!`/`tracing::error!`","newString":"- [x] #4 - Replace `println!/eprintln!` with structured logging (tracing crate)\n  - Added tracing + tracing-subscriber deps, initialized in main()\n  - Replaced gui/mod.rs println with tracing::info!, config/manager.rs eprintln with tracing::warn!\n  - Note: src/ui/ and src/inspect/ println calls are intentional CLI user output, not logging","originalFile":"# Ralph Fix Plan\n\n## High Priority (Bugs)\n\n- [x] #2 - Replace unsafe `unwrap()` calls with proper error handling in `src/gui/routes.rs`\n  - Replaced 4x `serde_json::to_value().unwrap()` with `map_err` in analyze endpoints\n  - Replaced 2x `.as_ref().unwrap()` with `.ok_or(...)` in `clean_file`\n- [x] #7 - Fix temp file memory leak from `Box::leak()` in `src/gui/routes.rs`\n  - Added `temp_paths: Vec<PathBuf>` to `AppState` with `Drop` impl for cleanup\n  - Replaced `Box::leak`/`mem::forget` with `tmp_path.keep()` + tracking in state\n\n## High Priority (Code Quality)\n\n- [ ] #4 - Replace `println!/eprintln!` with structured logging (tracing crate)\n  - At minimum: `src/gui/mod.rs` line 46 uses `println!`\n  - Scan entire codebase for println/eprintln and replace with `tracing::info!`/`tracing::error!`\n\n## Medium Priority (Features - Backend)\n\n- [ ] #6 - Expose FLAC and AAC format support in CLI\n  - Check if symphonia already decodes these; add encoder support if missing\n  - Update CLI help text and format detection in `src/audio/io.rs`\n- [ ] #12 - Add `--dry-run` flag to clean command\n  - Add flag to CLI args in `src/cli/`\n  - Run detection/analysis but skip writing output file\n- [ ] #13 - Add export report feature (JSON and PDF)\n  - JSON export of analysis + cleaning results\n  - PDF can be deferred if no easy crate available\n- [ ] #19 - Add streaming support for large audio files\n  - Chunked reading/processing to avoid loading entire file into memory\n\n## Medium Priority (Features - GUI)\n\n- [ ] #1 - Add spectrogram visualization for cleaned audio\n  - Backend: add `/api/spectrogram/cleaned` endpoint (similar to `/api/waveform/cleaned`)\n  - Frontend: render cleaned spectrogram alongside original\n- [ ] #5 - Add upload progress indicator and file size validation\n  - Frontend: show upload progress bar, validate max file size before upload\n  - Backend: already has 500MB limit, surface it to frontend\n- [ ] #10 - Display verification results and quality scores in GUI\n- [ ] #11 - Add configuration and preset selection UI\n- [ ] #14 - Add audio playback controls in GUI\n- [ ] #9 - Add before/after audio comparison timeline\n- [ ] #20 - Add detailed metadata tag viewer in GUI\n\n## Low Priority (Infrastructure)\n\n- [ ] #3 - Implement comprehensive test suite\n  - Unit tests for detection modules, sanitization pipeline, DSP primitives\n  - Integration tests for CLI commands\n- [ ] #16 - Add React error boundaries for component crashes\n- [ ] #8 - Add session persistence across page refreshes\n- [ ] #17 - Add code coverage reporting (CI)\n- [ ] #15 - Add release artifact publishing on git tags (CI)\n- [ ] #18 - Optimize spectral operations to reuse STFT computations\n\n## Completed\n- [x] Project enabled for Ralph\n\n## Working Notes\n- All issues sourced from GitHub issues list (as of 2026-03-10)\n- Issues labeled `ralph-task`: #2, #3, #4, #6, #7, #12, #15, #16, #17, #18\n- After completing an issue, run `gh issue close <number>` to close it\n- Always run `cargo check --all-targets && cargo clippy --all-targets -- -D warnings && cargo fmt --all --check` before committing\n- Commit format: conventional commits, single line, no co-authorship trailers\n","structuredPatch":[{"oldStart":11,"oldLines":9,"newStart":11,"newLines":10,"lines":[" "," ## High Priority (Code Quality)"," ","-- [ ] #4 - Replace `println!/eprintln!` with structured logging (tracing crate)","-  - At minimum: `src/gui/mod.rs` line 46 uses `println!`","-  - Scan entire codebase for println/eprintln and replace with `tracing::info!`/`tracing::error!`","+- [x] #4 - Replace `println!/eprintln!` with structured logging (tracing crate)","+  - Added tracing + tracing-subscriber deps, initialized in main()","+  - Replaced gui/mod.rs println with tracing::info!, config/manager.rs eprintln with tracing::warn!","+  - Note: src/ui/ and src/inspect/ println calls are intentional CLI user output, not logging"," "," ## Medium Priority (Features - Backend)"," "]}],"userModified":false,"replaceAll":false}}
